SIMPLE: keynote
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Keynote
<hw>Key"note`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>The tonic or first tone of the scale in which a
piece or passage is written; the fundamental tone of the chord, to which
all the modulations of the piece are referred; -- called also
<altname>key tone</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The fundamental fact or idea; that which gives the
key; <as>as, the <ex>keynote</ex> of a policy or a
sermon</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Keyseat</ent>⟦br⟧
